16000031.name: MR. P
16000031.description: Mr. P is a disgruntled luggage handler who angrily hurls suitcases at opponents. His Super calls robo-porters to help him.

16000032.name: MAX
16000032.description: Max goes fast! Her attack is a fast-firing blaster. Her Super speeds up her and allies!

16000034.name: JACKY
16000034.description: Jacky works her Jackhammer to shake up the ground and nearby enemies. Her Super pulls in nearby foes, leaving them in the dust!

videos.name: Jacky's Main Attack
videos.description: Check out how Jacky attacks.

videos.name: Jacky's Super Attack
videos.description: Check out how Jacky uses the Super.

16000035.name: GALE
16000035.description: Gale is a tireless handyman who gets no rest. He blasts foes with a wide shot of wind and snow and his Super pushes them back with a huge gust of wind!

videos.name: Gale's Main Attack
videos.description: Check out how Gale attacks.

videos.name: Gale's Super Attack

16000036.name: NANI
16000036.description: Nani loves her friends and looks over them with a watchful lens. She handles threats with angled shots, and her Super allows Nani to commandeer her pal Peep, who goes out with a bang!

videos.name: Nani's Main Attack
videos.description: Check out how Nani attacks.

videos.name: Nani's Super Attack
videos.description: Check out how Nani uses the Super.

16000037.name: SPROUT
16000037.description: Sprout was built to plant life, launching bouncy Seed Bombs with reckless love. Its Super creates a plant-based obstacle!

videos.name: Sprout's Main Attack
videos.description: Check out how Sprout attacks.

videos.name: Sprout's Super Attack
videos.description: Check out how Sprout uses the Super.

16000038.name: SURGE
16000038.description: He's a Protector with a penchant for parties. Surge attacks foes with energy drink blasts that split in two on contact. His Super upgrades his stats in 3 stages and comes complete with totally awesome body mods!

videos.name: Surge's Main Attack
videos.description: Check out how Surge attacks.

videos.name: Surge's Super Attack
videos.description: Check out how Surge uses the Super.

16000039.name: COLETTE
16000039.description: Colette is going to get you! She taxes opponents' health and has fancy moves to boot.

16000040.name: AMBER
16000040.description: Amber has always been a firebug. She loves to light up the world and any opponents that come at her!

16000041.name: LOU
16000041.description: Lou is a cool guy, literally! He can dole out all kinds of chill stuff. But watch your step on the ice, and be careful not to get brain freeze!

16000042.name: BYRON
16000042.description: Byron deals with potent medicaments, but never call him a snake oil salesman!

16000043.name: EDGAR
16000043.description: Let's face it, this is an angry kid. He also loves parkour.

16000044.name: COLONEL RUFFS
16000044.description: Ruffs fires twin shots of lasers that bounce off walls. His Super is a supply drop that can damage enemies in the drop zone and leaves a power up for your team to use.

16000045.name: STU
16000045.description: Stu is a stunt driver extraordinaire with gasoline in his veins! He makes a big entrance, burning serious rubber all over the stage.

16000046.name: BELLE
16000046.description: Belle inspires adoration in her gang, while her Electo-Rifle brings shock and awe to any opponent!

16000047.name: SQUEAK
16000047.description: As Col. Ruff's accidental creation, Squeak was born to play fetch!

16000048.name: GROM
16000048.description: Watchman Grom's priority is to keep guard. He throws his trusty radio at his enemies. His Super is a big bad bomb that breaks walls and pushes back enemies!

16000049.name: BUZZ
16000049.description: Buzz is the lifeguard at Velocirapids. He constantly scans for folks in trouble he can throw his torpedo buoy to, but his throws are rather overenthusiastic.

16000050.name: GRIFF
16000050.description: Griff is the proprietor of Starr Park's gift shop. Business is bad, but he still throws coins away - from his employees' tip jar!

16000051.name: ASH
16000051.description: Ash easily gets furious about all the junk he has to clean up. Dealing or receiving blows, even more so. The Fury makes him faster and more dangerous, but eventually he cools down.

16000052.name: MEG
16000052.description: Meg has a basic form and an advanced form where she hops inside her trusted Mecha. The Mecha loses health over time and has low healing ability. Destroying the Mecha returns Meg to her basic form.

16000053.name: LOLA
16000053.description: Despite being just a guide, Lola portrays herself as THE leading lady of Brawlywood. She attacks with her scarf and her Super is a channeled manifestation of her Ego.

16000054.name: FANG
16000054.description: Fang kicks first and he kicks fast. His main attack is a hefty kick that sends his shoe flying! Fang's Super is a powerful kick that will chain hit multiple enemies who are close together.

16000056.name: EVE
16000056.description: Eve believes that everyone can be valuable... as a resource for her babies.
